<body>
<table width="80%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
  <tr>
	<td width="50%">
		<div align="right"><img src="CityU_logo.gif" width="152" height="45" align="absbottom"></div></td>
	<td width="50%">
		<div align="left"><img src="com_Logo.jpg" align="absbottom"></div></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2"><div align="center"><img src="macnm_rb.gif" width="560" height="54"></div></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="2"><div align="center">
	<br>
        | <a href="index.cfm">Home</a>
		| <a href="Admission/index.cfm">Admissions</a> 
        | <a href="curriculum/index.cfm">Curriculum</a> 
        | <a href="staff/index.cfm">Staff</a>
		| <a href="students/index.cfm">Students</a> 
        | <a href="facilities/index.cfm">Facilities</a> 
        | </p></div></td>
  </tr>
</table>
<br>

<table width="60%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1">
  <tr>
    <td style="bodytext_darkgrey">As the first of its type in Hong Kong, this MA program offers courses 
      on latest human communication theories and cutting-edge new media technologies. 
      Since 1998, the program has enrolled twelve classes, each including mid-career 
      professionals with working experience in mass media, advertising, public 
      relations, marketing communication, corporate communication, government 
      or non-profit organizational communication, web and multimedia production 
      firms, and other communication sectors. 
      <p>The program offers both part-time and full-time modes of study. Part-time 
        students take 2-3 courses per semester to complete the study in 4 semesters 
        plus 1 summer whereas full-time students take 4 courses per semesters 
        to complete the study in 2 semesters plus 1 summer. Graduates from the 
        program are expected to become knowledgeable and skillful in planning, 
        designing, producing, and evaluating communication projects involving 
        the Internet and/or multimedia. 
		<span class="bodytext_cyan"><a href="curriculum/index.cfm">&lt;More 
        on curriculum&gt;</a></span></p>
      <p>There is one application exercise per year. The application period is open from 
	  December to February. Later applications may be considered when space is available. The admitted students will 
        begin classes in September of the same year. <span class="bodytext_cyan"><a href="Admission/index.cfm">&lt;More 
        on admissions&gt;</a></span></p>
      <p align="center"><font color="#660066"> 



The application period for 2011 entry will begin in mid-November 2010 as a tentative schedule. Please visit <a href="http://www.sgs.cityu.edu.hk/prospective/apply/procedures" target="_blank">here</a> to obtain more detailed information about the application process.


</p>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</body>
</html>
